A court in Egypt has sentenced 10 Islamist supporters of ousted president Mohammed Morsi's Muslim Brotherhood to death for inciting violence and blocking a road.

The men were sentenced in absentia at a court in the Nile Delta town of Banha following the incident last July.

Judge Hassan Fareed, presiding over the court, referred the sentence to the Grand Mufti, the highest Islamic authority, which is a legal requirement usually considered a formality. 

